I completely agree with the fundamental difference between scholarly and
 faith-driven perspectives.
 I used to think that learning Sanskrit might help me better understand
 the original texts, but the more I learn, the more I feel that there is
 a lot that is left to interpretation even in the original texts.
 It seems that a guru/traditional-perspective is often implicit in the interpret
ation of the texts.
 A lot of them having commentaries after commentaries (bhaashya) also seem
 to suggest that the older texts might have been used as teaching-notes
 rather than accurate descriptions of the world the way one might expect
 them to be in this age.
 
\end_layout

